## Issue Details
- **ID:** PAN-479
- **Title:** OpenRouter integration — API key settings + model selection in Mission Control
- **URL:** https://github.com/eltmon/panopticon-cli/issues/479

## Description
## Summary

Add OpenRouter as a provider for Mission Control conversations, enabling access to any model available on OpenRouter (including free models like Qwen 3.6) alongside native Claude models.

## Key Finding: No Proxy Needed

OpenRouter has a **native Anthropic Messages API endpoint** at `POST https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/messages` — their "Anthropic Skin" accepts any model ID from their catalog and translates the Anthropic format to whatever the target model needs.

**Setup for Claude Code CLI:**
```bash
ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=<openrouter-api-key>
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=""
```

Then pass `--model qwen/qwen3.6-plus:free` to Claude Code CLI. No `claude-code-router` or other proxy needed.

Sources:
- [OpenRouter Claude Code Integration](https://openrouter.ai/docs/guides/coding-agents/claude-code-integration)
- [OpenRouter Anthropic Messages API](https://openrouter.ai/docs/api/api-reference/anthropic-messages/create-messages)

## Requirements

### 1. Settings: OpenRouter API Key
- Add OpenRouter API key field to the Settings page
- Store in `~/.panopticon.env` (same as other secrets)
- Validate key on save (test with a lightweight API call)

### 2. Model Discovery from OpenRouter
- Fetch available models from OpenRouter API (`GET https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models`)
- Allow user to select which models they want available in the Mission Control model picker
- Store selected models in settings/DB
- Show model pricing info (cost per token) in the selection UI

### 3. Mission Control Model Picker Integration
- Extend ModelPicker dropdown to show both:
  - Native Claude models (current: Opus, Sonnet, Haiku via Claude CLI subscription)
  - OpenRouter models (user-selected subset)
- Group by provider in the dropdown (e.g., "Claude" section, "OpenRouter" section)
- Show per-model cost indicator in picker

### 4. Conversation Spawning with OpenRouter Models
- When an OpenRouter model is selected, the launcher script sets:
  ```bash
  export ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api
  export ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=<openrouter-key>
  export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=""
  ```
- Pass `--model <openrouter-model-id>` to Claude Code CLI (e.g., `qwen/qwen3.6-plus:free`)
- Native Claude models continue using the current flow (no env overrides)

### 5. Effort/Thinking Support
- Map OpenRouter model capabilities to effort picker
- Most non-Anthropic models don't support `--effort` — disable picker for those
- Claude models via OpenRouter may still support effort (test and confirm)

### 6. First Target Model
- **Qwen 3.6 Plus (free)**: `qwen/qwen3.6-plus:free` — https://openrouter.ai/qwen/qwen3.6-plus:free
- Validate full end-to-end flow with this model

## Files
- `src/dashboard/frontend/src/components/Settings/SettingsPage.tsx` — API key input
- `src/dashboard/frontend/src/components/chat/ModelPicker.tsx` — extend with OpenRouter models
- `src/dashboard/server/routes/conversations.ts` — provider-aware launcher script
- New: `src/dashboard/server/routes/settings.ts` or similar — API key storage endpoint
- New: `src/dashboard/server/services/openrouter-service.ts` — model discovery, API key validation

